A note, in the hand- writing of Casley, states that it was added to the Harleian Library on 5th January 1729; beyond which fact nothing is known of its previous history.

The ‘ Historia Britonum' commences on the reverse of a leaf, the former page of which is blank ; and is without title, rubrio, or colophon. This title appears to have been ‘ Incipit Computus.’
